The Opportunity
We are looking for an Analyst Quality Control (QC) to join the QC Chemistry team in Parkville (Australia) in this fixed term role until December 31, 2023. Reporting to the QC team leader or Specialist to you will perform a range of the chemistry, biochemistry and other assays to support the release of products
The Role
As the QC Analyst you will:
Support the team to ensure that the assays performed in each department are prepared and completed following Good Laboratory Practice (GLP);
Support the operational area to to prevent invalid assays and reduce Out of Specification (OOS) test results, and help investigate OOS test results, invalid assays ;
Recommend and implement improvements (under guidance and discussion with Team Leader or Specialist) to enhance quality within each functional area;
Help with the accurate completion, maintenance and upkeep of quality records and documents including procedures and work instructions;
Help maintain the work environment compliant with GMP guidelines including the washing, disinfection, heat sterilization and decontamination of materials and equipment following relevant procedures;
Work following all regulatory requirements, guidelines, policies, QC procedures and work instructions including Environment, Health & Safety (EHS) guidelines.
Your skills and experience
To be considered for this role you require:
Tertiary qualifications in an appropriate scientific discipline, applied science or biological technology; discipline or demonstrated laboratory experience;
Experience maintaining testing records;
Proficiency in computer systems for data entry and inquiry functions;
Experience in assay preparation;
Excellent scientific report writing skills.
Other Important things to note:
This role is based on a 73.5 hours per fortnight, although working hours can are set according to a rotating shift pattern. These shifts comprise day, afternoon and nights and some weekend work may be required.
You may undertake vaccination against the influenza virus.
How to apply: Please send us your resume and cover letter (in one document), which addresses the criteria above and includes reference number R-171181 by 14 August , 2022.
